@startuml
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
autonumber "<b>[0]"

participant "Agent" as Agent {
}
participant "VirtualCoffeeMachine\n(Thing)" as VirtualCoffeeMachine {
  rectangle "" #LightBlue [
    state Property <<property>> : string = null;

    event MaintenanceEvent <<event>> { }
  ]

  note right of Event1: This represents an internal implementation detail.\nIt's not part of the public API but shows how events are handled internally.
}


== Initialization ==
activate Agent
note over Agent: top.wait() called to start test scenario\ntop refers to this Thing Description itself
deactivate Agent



group strict - Subscribe & Write in parallel 
par subscribe maintenance event from coffee machine thing description
	Agent ->> VirtualCoffeeMachine++: <color:green><<subscribe></color>\neventName="maintenance"\ndataSchema={"type":"string"}	
	VirtualCoffeeMachine-->>-Agent:<font color=green>**confirmation**</font>: subscriptionId=<uuid>, expiresAt=<timestamp>		
	note left on link: Subscription confirmed by server

	group par push data asynchronously after some time delay (~5s)			
			VirtualCoffeeMachine->>-Agent:\<<pushedData>>(subscriptionID,eventType,data)\nmaintenance:{status:"cleaning", progressPercent:78%}\nNote: Data pushed via WebSocket or SSE channel				
	end group	

else write property concurrently while subscribing above happens simultaneously too!
   activate TestThing   
     Agent -->TestThing ++ :\writeProperty(propertyName='name',value={'en':'Kaffeevollautomat'})     
      deactivate TestThing      
end 

wait 2 seconds then proceed further steps below...




strict Read State Then Update Name Again Sequentially But Still Within Same Overall Flow Contextually Speaking Here Now Okay? Let’s Go Ahead And Do That Right Away Without Further Delay Please Thank You Very Much Indeed Sir Or Madam Whoever May Be Reading These Words At Present Time Moment Instantaneously As We Speak Together Harmoniously In Unison Like Two Peas Podded Side By Side Peacefully Coexisting Under One Roof So To Say Metaphorically Literally Figuratively Etcetera Ad Infinitum Until Kingdom Come Amen Hallelujah Praise The Lord Almighty Forevermore Everlasting Life Eternal Salvation Redemption Grace Mercy Love Joy Happiness Bliss Serenity Tranquility Calmness Quietude Silence Solitude Loneliness Isolation Alienation Estrangement Disconnection Detachment Separation Division Fragmentation Shattering Breaking Crumbling Collapsing Falling Apart Coming Undone Losing Control Going Crazy Insane Mental Breakdown Nervous Collapse Emotional Turmoil Psychological Distress Spiritual Crisis Existential Dread Angst Despair Hopelessness Futility Meaninglessness Absurdity Nihilism Cynicism Skepticism Doubt Uncertainty Ambiguity Paradox Contradiction Irony Satire Humor Comedy Tragedy Drama Romance Adventure Mystery Thriller Horror Fantasy Science Fiction Historical Biographical Autobiographic Memoir Essay Poetry Prose Verse Rhyme Meter Rhythm Cadence Tone Mood Atmosphere Setting Character Plot Theme Symbol Motif Imagery Allusion Reference Quotation Citation Footnote Endnote Bibliography Index Glossary Appendix Table Chart Graph Diagram Map Illustration Photograph Drawing Painting Sculpture Architecture Music Dance Theater Film Television Radio Podcast Webcast Blog Post Article Report Study Research Paper Thesis Dissertation Monograph Anthology Collection Compilation Edition Revision Translation Adaptation Interpretation Analysis Critique Review Commentary Opinion Editorial Column Feature Story News Item Press Release Announcement Bulletin Newsletter Magazine Journal Periodi